CommonFields.Title: Impact of Filler Surface Modification on Large Scale Mechanics of Styrene Butadiene/Silica Rubber Composites
Author: Stöckelhuber, K. W.
Svistkov, A. S.
Pelevin, A. G.
Heinrich, G.
CommonFields.Location: Leibniz-Institut für Polymerforschung Dresden e.V. , Hohe Strasse 6, D-01069 Dresden, Germany

Heating.Description: The curing package consists of 1.5 phr sulfur, 2 phr DPG (diphenylguanidine) and 1.5 phr CBS (n-cyclohexyl-2-benzothiazolesulfenamide).

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.Description: For TEM experiments, ultrathin sections of the rubber composite were cut by ultramicrotome at a temperature of about -100°C and the images were taken by a JEM 2010 transmission electron microscope

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: Dynamic mechanical analysis was performed with an Eplexor 2000N dynamic measurement system (Gabo Qualimeter, Ahlden, Germany) using a constant frequency of 10 Hz. The samples were analyzed in tension mode.

Differential_Scanning_Calorimetry.Description: The dielectric properties were measured with a broadband dielectric spectrometer, BDS 40 system, manufactured by Novocontrol GmbH, Germany. The investigations were performed on disk shaped rubber samples with a thickness of 2mm and a diameter of 20 mm.

Rheometery.Description: Flocculation measurements were carried out using amoving die rheometer (Scarabaeus SIS-V50, Langgons, Germany).

DynamicProperties.Description: Frequency mastercurve was made by using the time temperature superposition principle
